modules.description: Provides functions to parse, manipulate, and compare date ranges, including intersection and union operations. Works with custom date range records and time intervals represented as start and end timestamps. Used to schedule overlapping events and generate conflict-free timetables.

Converts between various calendar systems (Gregorian, Julian, French, Hebrew) and a serial day number (SDN) format, and computes moon phase data from SDN. Works with custom date types representing calendar dates and an enumerated type for moon phases. Enables precise date transformations for historical, astronomical, or cultural applications.
